<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-05-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="358" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d358">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Austria/13</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Acting Secretary of State</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-05-09">May 9,
                                    1932</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>I called in the Austrian Minister<note n="3" xml:id="d358fn3">
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PELG1">Edgar L. G.
                                    Prochnik</persName>.</note> to hand him the agreement as to the
                                moratorium, a copy of which is attached.<note n="4" xml:id="d358fn4">Not attached to file copy.</note> He said that he knew these
                                agreements had been given to others and was beginning to hope that
                                Austria had been forgotten. I pointed out to him the necessity of
                                haste in signing it to avoid complications and explained to him that
                                it was, after all, a routine matter. The Minister said he would
                                telegraph his Government, asking that he be appointed to sign.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_CWR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. R. Castle, Jr.</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>